&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/domains/who-benefits/people/david-tassillo/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/cybernetic-postliberalism/domains/who-benefits/people/david-tassillo/> ;
  schema:name "David Tassillo" ;
  schema:description "Lebanese-Canadian executive who served as President/COO of MindGeek alongside CEO Feras Antoon through the company's peak years, holding (with Antoon) 99.7% of MindGeek S.à.r.l. per Luxembourg's beneficial-ownership registry. The *Fleites v. MindGeek* complaint alleges this share was held on behalf of the controlling beneficial owner Bergmair as compensation for running day-to-day operations." ;
